    "narrative": "The premier play on our board today is **Corbin Carroll**, boasting an elite 85.94 score against Kremer. The combination of a favorable park shift (+16%) and the high-leverage #2 spot in the lineup creates a massive ceiling, and with SB being our primary scarcity target, his ability to exploit the matchups is paramount. Similarly, **Jose Caballero** (75.02) earns a spot start due to a significant +13% dynamic platoon edge against Kikuchi, making him a high-efficiency asset despite hitting in the bottom of the order. While **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Giancarlo Stanton** also benefit from the favorable wind conditions and Kikuchi\u2019s profile, **Jose Caballero** remains our most critical \"efficiency-per-dollar\" play to keep our SB category competitive.\n\nWe are navigating a treacherous slate of opposing arms today, as the presence of Eovaldi and Skenes necessitates caution. **James Wood** (48.27) faces a difficult test against Skenes, and while his leadoff position provides a +10% boost, his score remains marginal; we are playing him primarily for the stolen base potential. The closest call on our bench remains **Josh Naylor** (57.94), who barely edged out our more marginal infielders. While **Tyler Soderstrom** (52.69) and **Max Muncy** (43.71) face the stiff challenge of Eovaldi, the lack of available depth\u2014exacerbated by off-days for **Mickey Moniak**, **Brice Turang**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino**\u2014leaves us with limited flexibility to rotate in reserves like **Carson Williams** or **Dalton Rushing**. Owners should monitor the weather closely for the games in Toronto and Arlington, as any shifts could further compress the efficiency scores of our hitters facing the tougher right-handed starters.",
